FBIS4-14876 "drsov065_a_94013" FBIS-SOV-94-065 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UN Secretary General Departs UN Secretary General Departs LD0504095294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0937 GMT 5 Apr 94 LD0504095294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] [Text] Moscow 5 April, TASS -- U.N. Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali has described his talks with Russian leaders as constructive. Upon winding up his five-day official visit, he left here for Minsk on Tuesday. At the airport he was seen off by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. In a brief ITAR-TASS interview before departure, the U.N. chief said he postively assesses the results of the visit. Russia renders effective assistance to U.N. activities to keep peace and settle crisis situations, he emphasised.
